        <Parent_String>holders for drafting, drawing and writing [300168480], drafting, drawing and writing equipment by specific type [300168215], equipment for drafting, drawing, and writing [300168214], image-making equipment [300162803], equipment by process [300024659], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Handles for holding chalk, crayons, or charcoal, consisting of a split metal tube, usually double-ended, in which the material is secured by a ring that slides over the split end.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026701/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Houders waarmee krijt, kleurkrijt of houtskool kan worden vastgehouden en die bestaan uit een gespleten metalen buis, waarin meestal aan beide uiteinden tekenmateriaal door een ring, die over het gespleten uiteinde glijdt, kan worden vastgehouden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>可裝入粉筆、蠟筆、炭筆的握柄；內含一個細金屬管，末端可開闔(通常包括頭尾兩端)，可開闔的一端附有可滑動的圓環，能用於固定粉筆、蠟筆、炭筆。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
